## What

Add a detectPlatform() function to extractor.mjs that mirrors the bash implementation.

## Implementation

```javascript
function detectPlatform(url) {
    const patterns = {
        icloud: /(?:share\.)?icloud\.com\/photos/i,
        dropbox: /dropbox\.com\/(?:s|scl\/fi|sh)\//i,
        gphotos: /photos\.(?:app\.goo\.gl|google\.com\/share)/i,
        gdrive: /(?:drive|docs)\.google\.com\/(?:file\/d|open\?id)/i
    };

    for (const [platform, regex] of Object.entries(patterns)) {
        if (regex.test(url)) return platform;
    }
    return 'unknown';
}
```

## Why Regex in JS

Unlike bash where case patterns are idiomatic, JavaScript regex is:
- More expressive (non-capturing groups, case insensitivity)
- Easier to test in isolation
- Standard practice in the JS ecosystem

## Sync Requirement

This MUST return the same results as the bash detect_platform(). Consider:
1. A shared test suite that runs both implementations
2. A JSON config file both read (future enhancement)
3. CI job that verifies parity

## Usage in Extractor

```javascript
const platform = detectPlatform(url);
switch (platform) {
    case 'icloud':
        return await captureICloud(page, url);
    case 'dropbox':
        return await captureDropbox(page, url);
    case 'gphotos':
        return await captureGooglePhotos(page, url);
    case 'gdrive':
        return await captureGoogleDrive(page, url);
    default:
        throw new Error(`Unsupported platform: ${url}`);
}
```

## What

Add validation to ensure downloaded content is actually an image, not an HTML error page.

## Why This Is Critical

Dropbox and Google Drive can return HTML error pages with HTTP 200:
- Password-protected links return HTML login form
- Expired links return HTML error page
- Private files return HTML "request access" page

Without validation, giil would save HTML as "image.jpg" - a silent, confusing failure.

## Implementation: Two-Layer Validation

### Layer 1: Content-Type Header

```javascript
function validateContentType(response) {
    const contentType = response.headers()['content-type'] || '';
    const validTypes = [
        'image/jpeg', 'image/png', 'image/gif', 
        'image/webp', 'image/heic', 'image/heif',
        'application/octet-stream'  // Some CDNs use this
    ];

    // Reject HTML explicitly
    if (contentType.includes('text/html')) {
        throw new Error('CONTENT_TYPE_HTML: Server returned HTML, not image');
    }

    // Warn if unexpected but allow (some CDNs misconfigure)
    const isValid = validTypes.some(t => contentType.includes(t));
    return { valid: isValid, contentType };
}
```

### Layer 2: Magic Bytes Verification

```javascript
const MAGIC_BYTES = {
    jpeg: [0xFF, 0xD8, 0xFF],
    png: [0x89, 0x50, 0x4E, 0x47],
    gif: [0x47, 0x49, 0x46, 0x38],
    webp: [0x52, 0x49, 0x46, 0x46],  // "RIFF" (check for WEBP at offset 8)
    heic: [0x00, 0x00, 0x00],  // ftyp box (check for heic/mif1 later)
};

function validateMagicBytes(buffer) {
    const head = buffer.slice(0, 12);

    // Check JPEG
    if (head[0] === 0xFF && head[1] === 0xD8 && head[2] === 0xFF) {
        return 'jpeg';
    }

    // Check PNG
    if (head[0] === 0x89 && head[1] === 0x50 && head[2] === 0x4E && head[3] === 0x47) {
        return 'png';
    }

    // Check for HTML (starts with < or whitespace+<)
    const str = head.toString('utf8').trim();
    if (str.startsWith('<') || str.startsWith('<!')) {
        throw new Error('MAGIC_BYTES_HTML: Content appears to be HTML');
    }

    return 'unknown';  // Allow but log warning
}
```

## Error Mapping

- `CONTENT_TYPE_HTML` → Exit code 11 (AUTH_REQUIRED)
- `MAGIC_BYTES_HTML` → Exit code 11 (AUTH_REQUIRED)

## Testing

Create test cases with:
1. Valid JPEG buffer
2. Valid PNG buffer
3. HTML response with `Content-Type: image/jpeg` (malicious CDN)
4. HTML response with `Content-Type: text/html` (normal error page)

## What

Define a clear interface/contract that all platform adapters must implement. This ensures consistency and makes adding new platforms straightforward.

## Why JSDoc (Not TypeScript)

giil's extractor.mjs is vanilla JavaScript embedded in a bash heredoc. Converting to TypeScript would require:
1. Build step (tsc compilation)
2. Source maps for debugging
3. More complex distribution

JSDoc provides type checking in editors without runtime overhead.

## Interface Definition

```javascript
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ResolvedItem
 * @property {string} url - The original or normalized URL
 * @property {string} [directUrl] - Direct download URL if available
 * @property {string} [filename] - Suggested filename from URL/headers
 * @property {number} [index] - Position in album (for --all mode)
 */

/**
 * @typedef {Object} AcquireResult
 * @property {Buffer} bytes - The image data
 * @property {string} mime - MIME type (image/jpeg, image/png, etc.)
 * @property {string} platform - Platform identifier
 * @property {string} method - Capture method used
 * @property {number} tier - Strategy tier (1-4)
 * @property {string} [sourceUrl] - CDN URL where image was obtained
 * @property {boolean} [isPreview] - True if this is preview quality
 * @property {number} [width] - Image width in pixels
 * @property {number} [height] - Image height in pixels
 */

/**
 * @typedef {Object} AcquireContext
 * @property {import('playwright').Page} page - Playwright page instance
 * @property {number} timeout - Timeout in milliseconds
 * @property {boolean} debug - Whether debug mode is enabled
 */

/**
 * @typedef {Object} PlatformAdapter
 * @property {'icloud'|'dropbox'|'gphotos'|'gdrive'} id - Platform identifier
 * @property {(url: string) => boolean} match - Test if URL belongs to this platform
 * @property {(url: string) => string} normalize - Normalize URL to canonical form
 * @property {(url: string, opts: {all: boolean}) => Promise<ResolvedItem[]>} resolveItems - Resolve single item or album
 * @property {(item: ResolvedItem, ctx: AcquireContext) => Promise<AcquireResult>} acquire - Acquire image bytes
 */
```

## Usage Pattern

```javascript
/** @type {PlatformAdapter} */
const dropboxAdapter = {
    id: 'dropbox',

    match(url) {
        return /dropbox\.com\/(?:s|scl\/fi|sh)\//.test(url);
    },

    normalize(url) {
        return url.replace(/[&?](dl|raw)=[01]/g, '') + '&raw=1';
    },

    async resolveItems(url, { all }) {
        // Dropbox doesn't support album mode via web
        return [{ url: this.normalize(url) }];
    },

    async acquire(item, ctx) {
        // Direct download, no Playwright needed
        const response = await fetch(item.url);
        return {
            bytes: Buffer.from(await response.arrayBuffer()),
            mime: response.headers.get('content-type'),
            platform: 'dropbox',
            method: 'direct',
            tier: 1
        };
    }
};
```

## Benefits

1. **Self-Documenting**: IDE shows types and descriptions
2. **Consistency**: All platforms implement same interface
3. **Testability**: Can mock adapters for unit tests
4. **Extensibility**: Adding new platform = implementing interface

## What

Add polite delays between requests when downloading multiple photos in album mode.

## Why This Matters

1. **Don't hammer servers** - Rapid-fire requests can trigger rate limiting or bans
2. **Be a good citizen** - Cloud providers have ToS about automated access
3. **Reliability** - Slower, polite access is more likely to succeed long-term
4. **Avoid detection** - Rate limiting makes giil look less like a bot

## Default Behavior

| Scenario | Delay |
|----------|-------|
| Between album photos | 1 second |
| After rate limit (429) | Exponential backoff (2s, 4s, 8s) |
| After server error (5xx) | 3 seconds, then retry |

## Implementation

```javascript
const ALBUM_DELAY_MS = 1000;  // 1 second between photos
const MAX_RETRIES = 3;

async function downloadAlbumWithRateLimit(photos, context) {
    const results = [];

    for (let i = 0; i < photos.length; i++) {
        // Polite delay between photos (skip first)
        if (i > 0) {
            await sleep(ALBUM_DELAY_MS);
        }

        let retries = 0;
        while (retries < MAX_RETRIES) {
            try {
                const result = await downloadPhoto(photos[i], context);
                results.push(result);
                break;
            } catch (e) {
                if (e.statusCode === 429) {
                    const backoff = Math.pow(2, retries + 1) * 1000;
                    console.error(`[giil] Rate limited, waiting ${backoff/1000}s...`);
                    await sleep(backoff);
                    retries++;
                } else if (e.statusCode >= 500) {
                    console.error(`[giil] Server error, retrying in 3s...`);
                    await sleep(3000);
                    retries++;
                } else {
                    throw e;  // Non-retryable error
                }
            }
        }
    }

    return results;
}

function sleep(ms) {
    return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));
}
```

## CLI Override

Allow power users to adjust delay:

```bash
# Faster (risky)
giil "https://..." --all --delay 500

# Slower (safer)
giil "https://..." --all --delay 3000

# Parallel downloads (future enhancement)
giil "https://..." --all --jobs 3 --delay 500
```

## Per-Platform Considerations

| Platform | Notes |
|----------|-------|
| iCloud | Conservative - Apple may block aggressive access |
| Dropbox | No browser = fast already, minimal delay needed |
| Google Photos | Moderate - Google has good rate limiting |
| Google Drive | Conservative - API quotas are strict |

## Progress Indication

Show download progress with rate limit info:

```
[giil] Downloading album: 12 photos
[giil] [1/12] Downloading photo 1... done (2.1 MB)
[giil] [2/12] Downloading photo 2... done (1.8 MB)
[giil] [3/12] Downloading photo 3... rate limited, waiting 2s...
[giil] [3/12] Downloading photo 3... done (2.4 MB)
```

## Testing

Add test for rate limit handling:

```javascript
it('respects rate limiting', async () => {
    const mockServer = setupMockServerWithRateLimit();
    const results = await downloadAlbum(mockServer.url, { all: true });

    // Verify delays were applied
    expect(mockServer.requestTimestamps.length).toBeGreaterThan(1);
    const delays = computeDelays(mockServer.requestTimestamps);
    expect(Math.min(...delays)).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(ALBUM_DELAY_MS);
});
```

## What

Capture Google Photos CDN URLs during page load and extract the base URL for full-resolution download.

## The Strategy

1. Install network interceptor BEFORE navigation
2. Capture all `lh3.googleusercontent.com/pw/` URLs
3. Extract base URL (everything before the `=` size modifier)
4. Download full resolution using `{baseUrl}=s0`

## Implementation

```javascript
async function captureGooglePhotos(page, url) {
    const cdnUrls = new Set();

    // Install network interceptor BEFORE navigation
    page.on('response', async (response) => {
        const respUrl = response.url();

        // Capture Google Photos CDN URLs
        if (respUrl.includes('lh3.googleusercontent.com/pw/')) {
            // Extract base URL (before size modifier)
            const baseUrl = respUrl.split('=')[0];
            cdnUrls.add(baseUrl);
        }
    });

    // Navigate to the share page
    await page.goto(url, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' });

    // Wait for image to load (use element presence, not networkidle)
    await Promise.race([
        page.waitForSelector('[data-latest-bg], .RY3tic, img[src*="googleusercontent"]', 
            { timeout: 15000 }).catch(() => {}),
        page.waitForTimeout(5000)  // Fallback timeout
    ]);

    // Get the best URL (prefer largest if multiple)
    if (cdnUrls.size === 0) {
        throw new Error('No Google Photos CDN URL found');
    }

    // Use the first captured URL (for single photo)
    // For albums, we'd iterate through all
    const baseUrl = Array.from(cdnUrls)[0];
    const fullResUrl = `${baseUrl}=s0`;

    // Download full resolution directly
    const response = await fetch(fullResUrl);
    if (!response.ok) {
        throw new Error(`Failed to download: HTTP ${response.status}`);
    }

    return {
        bytes: Buffer.from(await response.arrayBuffer()),
        mime: response.headers.get('content-type'),
        platform: 'gphotos',
        method: 'url-extraction',
        tier: 1,
        sourceUrl: fullResUrl
    };
}
```

## Size Modifier Reference

| Modifier | Result |
|----------|--------|
| `=w1042-h862-no` | Constrained to 1042×862 |
| `=w0` | Full width |
| `=s0` | **Original size** |
| `=w4000` | Capped at 4000px or original |

## Why `=s0`?

The `s` parameter specifies "size" without aspect ratio constraints. `=s0` means "size 0" which Google interprets as "original/unlimited".

## Error Handling

```javascript
// Detect private album (redirects to login)
if (page.url().includes('accounts.google.com')) {
    throw new Error('AUTH_REQUIRED: Album is private. Only public shares are supported.');
}

// Detect empty album
if (cdnUrls.size === 0 && await page.$('.empty-album-message')) {
    throw new Error('NOT_FOUND: Album appears to be empty.');
}
```

## What

Support downloading all photos from a shared Google Photos album using the `--all` flag.

## Strategy: Multi-Signal Approach

Album detection is fragile because Google's class names change. Use multiple signals:

### Signal 1: Network Traffic (Most Reliable)
Collect all unique `lh3.googleusercontent.com/pw/` base URLs during page load.

```javascript
const albumUrls = new Set();

page.on('response', (response) => {
    const url = response.url();
    if (url.includes('lh3.googleusercontent.com/pw/')) {
        albumUrls.add(url.split('=')[0]);  // Base URL
    }
});
```

### Signal 2: Semantic Selectors (More Stable)
```javascript
const thumbnailSelectors = [
    // Semantic (preferred)
    '[role="listitem"] a',
    'a[aria-label*="photo" i]',
    '[role="img"]',

    // Observed structures (fallback)
    '[data-latest-bg]',
    '.RY3tic',
    '[style*="background-image"]'
];
```

### Signal 3: Background Image URLs
```javascript
async function extractBackgroundUrls(page) {
    return await page.evaluate(() => {
        const urls = [];
        document.querySelectorAll('[style*="background-image"]').forEach(el => {
            const style = el.style.backgroundImage;
            const match = style.match(/url\("([^"]+lh3\.googleusercontent[^"]+)"\)/);
            if (match) urls.push(match[1].split('=')[0]);
        });
        return urls;
    });
}
```

## Implementation

```javascript
async function captureGooglePhotosAlbum(page, url) {
    const results = [];
    const collectedUrls = new Set();

    // Install interceptor for thumbnails
    page.on('response', (response) => {
        const respUrl = response.url();
        if (respUrl.includes('lh3.googleusercontent.com/pw/')) {
            collectedUrls.add(respUrl.split('=')[0]);
        }
    });

    await page.goto(url, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' });

    // Wait for thumbnails to load
    await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle', { timeout: 15000 }).catch(() => {});

    // Scroll to load more thumbnails (if lazy-loaded)
    await scrollToLoadAll(page);

    // Combine with background image extraction
    const bgUrls = await extractBackgroundUrls(page);
    bgUrls.forEach(u => collectedUrls.add(u));

    // Download each unique URL with =s0
    let index = 1;
    for (const baseUrl of collectedUrls) {
        try {
            const fullUrl = `${baseUrl}=s0`;
            const response = await fetch(fullUrl);

            if (!response.ok) continue;

            results.push({
                bytes: Buffer.from(await response.arrayBuffer()),
                platform: 'gphotos',
                method: 'url-extraction',
                tier: 1,
                sourceUrl: fullUrl,
                index: index++
            });
        } catch (err) {
            console.error(`[giil] Photo ${index} failed: ${err.message}`);
            // Continue to next photo
        }
    }

    return results;
}

async function scrollToLoadAll(page, maxScrolls = 10) {
    for (let i = 0; i < maxScrolls; i++) {
        const prevHeight = await page.evaluate(() => document.body.scrollHeight);
        await page.evaluate(() => window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight));
        await page.waitForTimeout(1000);
        const newHeight = await page.evaluate(() => document.body.scrollHeight);
        if (newHeight === prevHeight) break;  // No more content
    }
}
```

## Output (--json mode)

Each photo outputs a separate JSON line:
```json
{"path": "gphotos_20260103_142245_001.jpg", "platform": "gphotos", "method": "url-extraction", ...}
{"path": "gphotos_20260103_142246_002.jpg", "platform": "gphotos", "method": "url-extraction", ...}
```

## Edge Cases

1. **Large albums**: Scroll pagination to load all thumbnails
2. **Videos in album**: Skip with warning (or `--include-videos`)
3. **Private album**: Detect login redirect, fail with clear message

## What

Extract the file ID from various Google Drive URL formats.

## Implementation

```javascript
function extractGoogleDriveFileId(url) {
    const patterns = [
        /\/file\/d\/([a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)/,      // /file/d/{id}/view
        /\/open\?id=([a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)/,       // /open?id={id}
        /[?&]id=([a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)/            // ?id={id} or &id={id}
    ];

    for (const pattern of patterns) {
        const match = url.match(pattern);
        if (match) return match[1];
    }
    return null;
}
```

## URL Format Examples

| Input URL | Extracted ID |
|-----------|--------------|
| `https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ABC123xyz/view` | `1ABC123xyz` |
| `https://drive.google.com/open?id=1ABC123xyz` | `1ABC123xyz` |
| `https://drive.google.com/uc?id=1ABC123xyz&export=download` | `1ABC123xyz` |

## Error Handling

```javascript
const fileId = extractGoogleDriveFileId(url);
if (!fileId) {
    throw new Error('USAGE_ERROR: Could not extract file ID from Google Drive URL');
}
```

## What

Detect when a Google Drive file requires authentication and provide clear, actionable error messages.

## Detection Strategy

### 1. Login Redirect Detection
```javascript
async function checkDriveAuth(page, fileId) {
    const viewUrl = `https://drive.google.com/file/d/${fileId}/view`;
    await page.goto(viewUrl, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded', timeout: 15000 });

    // Check for login redirect
    const currentUrl = page.url();
    if (currentUrl.includes('accounts.google.com')) {
        throw new DriveAuthError('File requires authentication. Not publicly shared.');
    }

    // Check for "request access" page
    const requestAccessBtn = await page.$('button:has-text("Request access")');
    if (requestAccessBtn) {
        throw new DriveAuthError('File is restricted. Owner must grant access.');
    }
}
```

### 2. API Response Detection
```javascript
// Some Drive URLs return 200 with HTML error page
async function validateDriveResponse(buffer) {
    const text = buffer.toString('utf8', 0, 1000);

    if (text.includes('accounts.google.com/ServiceLogin')) {
        throw new DriveAuthError('Login required');
    }

    if (text.includes('Request access') || text.includes('You need permission')) {
        throw new DriveAuthError('Access denied');
    }

    if (text.includes('Sorry, the file you have requested does not exist')) {
        throw new DriveNotFoundError('File not found or deleted');
    }
}
```

## Error Messages

### Not Publicly Shared
```
[giil] Error: Google Drive file is not publicly shared
[giil]
[giil] The file owner must:
[giil]   1. Right-click the file in Google Drive
[giil]   2. Click "Share" → "General access"
[giil]   3. Change "Restricted" to "Anyone with the link"
[giil]   4. Click "Done"
[giil]
[giil] Then try again with the same URL.
```

### File Not Found
```
[giil] Error: Google Drive file not found
[giil]
[giil] The file may have been:
[giil]   - Deleted by the owner
[giil]   - Moved to a different location
[giil]   - The URL may be incorrect
```

## Exit Code Mapping

| Scenario | Exit Code |
|----------|-----------|
| Login redirect | 11 (AUTH_REQUIRED) |
| Request access page | 11 (AUTH_REQUIRED) |
| File not found | 12 (NOT_FOUND) |
| Download quota | 10 (NETWORK_ERROR) |

## What

Implement the multi-tier capture strategy for downloading images from Google Drive.

## Problem

After detecting that a file IS publicly shared (hdm.4.2), we need to actually download it. Google Drive has multiple methods with varying reliability:

| Method | Quality | Reliability | Notes |
|--------|---------|-------------|-------|
| Download button click | Original | Medium | Button may not appear immediately |
| Direct URL (`/uc?export=download`) | Original | Low | Often 403s after 2024 changes |
| Thumbnail URL (`/thumbnail?sz=w4000`) | High but not original | Medium | Capped at 4000px |
| Playwright screenshot | Rendered | Always works | Last resort |

## Implementation

```javascript
async function captureGoogleDrive(page, fileId) {
    // TIER 1: Download button
    const downloadBtn = await page.$(
        'button[aria-label="Download"], [data-tooltip="Download"]'
    );
    if (downloadBtn) {
        const downloadPromise = page.waitForEvent('download', { timeout: 10000 });
        await downloadBtn.click();
        const download = await downloadPromise;
        const buffer = await download.path().then(p => readFileSync(p));
        return { bytes: buffer, method: 'download-button', tier: 1 };
    }

    // TIER 2: Direct download URL
    try {
        const directUrl = `https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=${fileId}`;
        const response = await fetch(directUrl, { redirect: 'follow' });

        // Check if we got HTML instead of image
        const contentType = response.headers.get('content-type');
        if (contentType?.startsWith('image/')) {
            return { 
                bytes: Buffer.from(await response.arrayBuffer()), 
                method: 'direct-url', 
                tier: 2 
            };
        }
    } catch (e) {
        console.error('[giil] Direct download failed:', e.message);
    }

    // TIER 3: Thumbnail endpoint with max size
    try {
        const thumbUrl = `https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=${fileId}&sz=w4000`;
        const response = await fetch(thumbUrl);
        if (response.ok) {
            const buffer = Buffer.from(await response.arrayBuffer());
            // Validate it's actually an image
            if (buffer[0] === 0xFF && buffer[1] === 0xD8) { // JPEG magic
                return { 
                    bytes: buffer, 
                    method: 'thumbnail', 
                    tier: 3,
                    isPreview: true  // Mark as potentially lower quality
                };
            }
        }
    } catch (e) {
        console.error('[giil] Thumbnail download failed:', e.message);
    }

    // TIER 4: Playwright screenshot of image element
    const imgElement = await page.$('img[src*="googleusercontent"]');
    if (imgElement) {
        const buffer = await imgElement.screenshot({ type: 'png' });
        return { bytes: buffer, method: 'element-screenshot', tier: 4 };
    }

    // TIER 5: Viewport screenshot (last resort)
    const buffer = await page.screenshot({ type: 'png' });
    return { bytes: buffer, method: 'viewport-screenshot', tier: 5 };
}
```

## Large File Handling (>100MB)

Google shows a virus scan warning for large files. We need to handle this:

```javascript
// Check for virus scan warning and click through
const virusWarning = await page.$('form#download-form');
if (virusWarning) {
    console.error('[giil] Large file detected, attempting virus scan bypass...');
    const confirmBtn = await page.$('a[href*="confirm="]');
    if (confirmBtn) {
        const downloadPromise = page.waitForEvent('download', { timeout: 30000 });
        await confirmBtn.click();
        const download = await downloadPromise;
        // ... handle download
    }
}
```

## Quality Warning

If using tier 3 (thumbnail) or higher, output a warning:

```javascript
if (result.tier >= 3) {
    console.error('[giil] Warning: Using fallback method. Image may not be full resolution.');
}
```

## Success Criteria

- [ ] Download button works when visible
- [ ] Direct URL works for simple files
- [ ] Thumbnail fallback captures viewable content
- [ ] Screenshot fallback always succeeds
- [ ] Large file virus scan handled
- [ ] Quality warning shown for fallback methods

## What

Set up a unit test framework for testing pure functions without network or browser.

## Scope

Test these functions in isolation:
- `detect_platform()` / `detectPlatform()` - Platform detection
- `normalize_dropbox_url()` - URL normalization
- `extractGoogleDriveFileId()` - File ID parsing
- `validateContentType()` - MIME type validation
- `validateMagicBytes()` - Binary header checking
- `formatOutput()` - JSON schema formatting
- `getUniqueFilename()` - Filename generation

## Test Framework Choice

**Option A: Node.js native test runner (recommended)**
```bash
# Node.js 18+ has built-in test runner
node --test tests/*.test.mjs
```

Pros:
- Zero dependencies
- Fast startup
- Native assertion library

**Option B: Vitest/Jest**
More features but adds dependencies to a zero-dep tool.

**Recommendation: Node.js native test runner**

## Implementation

### File Structure
```
scripts/
└── tests/
    ├── platform-detection.test.mjs
    ├── url-normalization.test.mjs
    ├── content-validation.test.mjs
    └── output-formatting.test.mjs
```

### Example Test: Platform Detection
```javascript
// scripts/tests/platform-detection.test.mjs
import { describe, it } from 'node:test';
import assert from 'node:assert';
import { detectPlatform } from '../../extractor-functions.mjs';

describe('detectPlatform', () => {
    it('detects iCloud share URLs', () => {
        assert.equal(detectPlatform('https://share.icloud.com/photos/abc123'), 'icloud');
        assert.equal(detectPlatform('https://www.icloud.com/photos/#abc123'), 'icloud');
    });

    it('detects Dropbox URLs', () => {
        assert.equal(detectPlatform('https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/xxx/photo.png?dl=0'), 'dropbox');
        assert.equal(detectPlatform('https://www.dropbox.com/s/xxx/photo.png'), 'dropbox');
    });

    it('detects Google Photos URLs', () => {
        assert.equal(detectPlatform('https://photos.app.goo.gl/abc123'), 'gphotos');
        assert.equal(detectPlatform('https://photos.google.com/share/abc?key=xyz'), 'gphotos');
    });

    it('detects Google Drive URLs', () => {
        assert.equal(detectPlatform('https://drive.google.com/file/d/xyz/view'), 'gdrive');
        assert.equal(detectPlatform('https://drive.google.com/open?id=xyz'), 'gdrive');
    });

    it('returns unknown for unsupported URLs', () => {
        assert.equal(detectPlatform('https://example.com/photo.jpg'), 'unknown');
    });
});
```

